                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>JAMES FOX. I <rs id="t18280110-213-viclabel1119" type="occupation">keep a cheesemonger's-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-213-victim1276 t18280110-213-viclabel1119"></join>, on the <placeName id="t18280110-213-crimeloc1120">Pavement, Moorfields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-213-crimeloc1120" type="placeName" value="Pavement, Moorfields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-213-crimeloc1120" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-213-off1117 t18280110-213-crimeloc1120"></join>. About six o'clock in the evening of the 8th of January, the officer brought the prisoner in with this ham, which I had seen safe on the door-post, a quarter of an hour before.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BODKIN. Q. Was it outside the door? A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-213-person1277">
                  GEORGE 
                  WILLIAM BENNETT
               <interp inst="t18280110-213-person1277" type="surname" value="WILLIAM BENNETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-213-person1277" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-213-person1277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 8th of January, about five o'clock, I saw the prisoners with another person in Chiswell-street; they tried about fifty shops - I watched them to the Pavement, saw Hanson go to the shop, lift up the ham, and take it away down Short-street - I followed, and took Hanson - I heard one of them whistle, which I think was Malvaney, as he was near the door-post, and I think he was going to take another ham. I heard one say it was all right.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. If you followed Hanson directly, could you see what the others were doing? A. No; but as I brought Hanson back, Malvaney was at the top of Short-street - Harrison took him; he was at the door when I followed Harrison.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-213-person1278">
                  THOMAS 
                  HARRISON
               <interp inst="t18280110-213-person1278" type="surname" value="HARRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-213-person1278" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-213-person1278" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Bennett; his evidence is correct - I took Malvaney; he told me if I would go to his mother, she would give me a sovereign, and make all right.</p>
               <p>HANSON'S Defence. A person came to me, and asked me to carry the ham to Blackfriars.</p>
               <p>HANSON - <rs id="t18280110-213-verdict1121" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280110-213-verdict1121" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280110-213-punish1122" type="punishmentDescription">
